definition.value: Fixed sarcastic grimace and anxious expression. Caused by spasms of the masseter and other facial muscles.
Hypopnea is referring to breathing that is abnormally shallow.
An abnormal concentration of insulin in the body.
A decreased concentration of insulin in the blood.

label.value: Abnormal size of the dental root

definition.value: Clinical phenotype characterized by delayed bleeding accelerated break down of blood clot (fibrinolysis)

label.value: Decrease in high molecular weight von Willebrand factor Multimers

definition.value: A decrease in high molecular weight von Willebrand factor multimers.

label.value: Decreased level of heparin co-factor II

definition.value: An abnormality of coagulation related to a decreased concentration of heparin co-factor II
Decrease of these levels result in increased inhibition of fibrinolysis and reduced inhibition of coagulation
A decreased level of Plasminogen
Thrombomodulin is a cofactor in the thrombin induced activation of Protein C. In the case of deficiency there will be less Protein C and tendency to clot

label.value: Decreased level of tissue plasminogen activator

definition.value: The tPA protein catalyzes the conversion of plasiminogen to plasmin, and thus break down of clots. When there is a deficiency there will be an increase of thrombosis
Abnormal bleeding related to a procedure or trauma which does not start at the time of the initial insult, but after delay by at least 24 hours.
Deficiency of factor XIII subunit A, leading to a reduced factor XIII activity. Activated Factor XIII cross-links fibrin polymers solidifying the clot.
Deficiency of factor XIII subunit B, leading to a reduced factor XIII activity. Activated Factor XIII cross-links fibrin polymers solidifying the clot.
The presence of intraceullar inclusion bodies (aggregates of stainable substances, usually proteins) in leukocytes.
Increased degradation of fibrin, associated with clot instability and bleeding

label.value: Impaired binding of factor VIII to VWF

definition.value: Impaired binding of factor VIII to von Willebrand Factor. This is determined using a modified ELISA assay.
An impairment of the migration of neutrophils towards chemoattractants as part of the innate immune response

label.value: Increased plasma vitamin K epoxide after vitamin K supplementation

definition.value: Increased plasma vitamin K epoxide after vitamin K supplementation is present in VKCFD (vitamin K-dependent clotting factor deficiency) type 2, but not in VKCFD type 1.

label.value: Increased ratio of VWF propeptide to VWF antigen

definition.value: An increased VWF propeptide to VWF antigen indicates that deficiency of VWF is not due to impaired synthesis but due to rapid clearance. The VWF propeptide is measured by ELISA.
Increased platelet agglutination in response to low-dose ristocetin

Abnormally increased length of time required for an in vitro clot to dissolve in the absence of the normal plasmin inhibitors. This test is a clinical assay used to measure fibrinolysis. The euglobulin fraction of plasma is precipitated and used to form clot by addition of thrombin; after clot forms the rate of clot breakdown (fibrinolysis) can be monitored.
Increased time to coagulation in the Russell's viper venom assay
Reduced activity of alpha-2-antiplasmin. This protein inactivates the protease plasmin that drives fibrinolysis.
Reduced antithrombin antigen. A reduced level of antithrombin may lead to an increased risk of thrombus formation.

Abnormally decreased length of time required for an in vitro clot to dissolve in the absence of the normal plasmin inhibitors. This test is a clinical assay used to measure fibrinolysis. The euglobulin fraction of plasma is precipitated and used to form clot by addition of thrombin; after clot forms the rate of clot breakdown (fibrinolysis) can be monitored.

Reduced activity of plasminogen activator inhibitor 1. This protein down-regulates fibrinolysis in the circulation by inhibiting the two major plasminogen activators: tissue-plasminogen activator and urokinase-plasminogen activator.
Reduced level of plasminogen activator inhibitor 1 antigen.
Reduced prothrombin antigen as measured by ELISA assay. Prothrombin is a vitamin K-dependent coagulation factor that is proteolytically cleaved to form thrombin.
Absence or underdevelopment of the nasopharyngeal adenoids.
Underdevelopment of the nasopharyngeal adenoids.
An abnormal increase in the size of nasopharyngeal adenoids.
